# Router on a stick steps

1. Create VLANs and assign access ports

# On the switch
vlan 10
 name SALES
vlan 20
 name IT
vlan 30
 name CORPORATE

interface range fa0/2 - 3
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 10

interface range fa0/4 - 5
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 20

interface range fa0/6 - 7
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 30

2. Configure trunk port to router

# Assuming router is connected to Fa0/1
interface fa0/1
 switchport trunk encapsulation dot1q
 switchport trunk allowed vlan 10,20,30
 switchport mode trunk

3. Configure router subinterfaces

# On the router
interface g0/0/0.10
 description VLAN 10 Gateway
 encapsulation dot1Q 10
 ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0

interface g0/0/0.20
 description VLAN 20 Gateway
 encapsulation dot1Q 20
 ip address 192.168.20.1 255.255.255.0

interface g0/0/0.30
 description VLAN 30 Gateway
 encapsulation dot1Q 30
 ip address 192.168.30.1 255.255.255.0

interface g0/0/0
 no shutdown

4. Configure DHCP pools

ip dhcp excluded-address 192.168.10.1 192.168.10.10
ip dhcp excluded-address 192.168.20.1 192.168.20.10
ip dhcp excluded-address 192.168.30.1 192.168.30.10

ip dhcp pool VLAN10
 network 192.168.10.0 255.255.255.0
 default-router 192.168.10.1
 dns-server 8.8.8.8

ip dhcp pool VLAN20
 network 192.168.20.0 255.255.255.0
 default-router 192.168.20.1
 dns-server 8.8.8.8

ip dhcp pool VLAN30
 network 192.168.30.0 255.255.255.0
 default-router 192.168.30.1
 dns-server 8.8.8.8

5. Optional, STP root bridge configuration

# Set switch as root for VLAN 1
spanning-tree vlan 1 priority 4096

6. Apply ACL to restrict VLAN 20 from accessing VLAN 10

access-list 100 deny ip 192.168.20.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.10.0 0.0.0.255
access-list 100 permit ip any any

interface g0/0/0.20
 ip access-group 100 in

Purpose: This ACL blocks any IP traffic from VLAN 20 to VLAN 10. All other traffic is allowed. Applied inbound to VLAN 20â€™s subinterface.
